  "texts": [
    "Tissue blocks are scanned with micro-computed tomography (µCT) and used to train the model (left).",
    "The trained model can be utilized for clinical cone-beam CT (CBCT) images using a patch-by-patch sliding window, the size of one patch is depicted with a green rectangle.",
    "In this case, predictions from all orthogonal planes were averaged converged to a solution with a slightly lower image quality.",
    "This led to more noisy prediction images, highlighting only the large-scale details.",
    "Clinical Image Quality on Dental ApplicationAn example of SR prediction on maxillofacial CBCT is shown in Fig. 8."
